OL,3,CLawrie Hooper resigns as Isle of Man
OL,4,Chealth minister
OL,6,FLawrie Hooper has resigned as the Isle
OL,7,Fof Man's Minister for Health and
OL,8,FSocial Care, claiming the Chief
OL,9,FMinister 'does not welcome my views'.
OL,11,FMr Hooper claimed Alfred Cannan's
OL,12,Fviews on the future of the health
OL,13,Fservice were 'increasingly diverged',
OL,14,Fadding that the Chief Minister is
OL,15,F'trying to privatise our health
OL,16,Fservice'.
OL,18,FThe Ramsey politician made the
OL,19,Fannouncement during a speech in the
OL,20,Ffirst parliamentary sitting of the new
OL,21,Fterm in Tynwald.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/7
